subSubSection.paragraph:
Recognition.
Large, blackish brown species (wing length 
6.3–7 mm
). Male (
Fig. 12
) eyes holoptic; thorax black setose, scutum densely brownish pruinescent, without distinct vittae; almost all mesonotal setae fine, hair-like (npl usually slightly stronger), long, presutural dc 3–5-serial, acr 2–3-serial; legs robust, entirely dark brown, hind femur entirely setose, hind tibia slender; wing brownish infuscate, halter brown; cerci directed anteriorly, short, prolonged nearly to middle of tergite 5, epandrium brownish. Female wing slightly darker and broader; mid femur with pennate posteroventral setae, hind femur with pennate anterodorsal and posteroventral setae, hind tibia with pennate setae dorsally and ventrally (on about middle).
